Document: JavaClassWrapper
Path: godot/classes/class_javaclasswrapper.rst
Summary: Provides access to the Java Native Interface for interacting with Java classes.

Inherits: Object

This class serves as a bridge between Godot's scripting environment and Java classes, enabling developers to call Java methods and access Java objects from within Godot projects. It is part of the Java Native Interface (JNI) integration in Godot, which allows for interoperability between Godot and Java-based applications or libraries.
---CHUNK---
Document: JavaClassWrapper
Path: godot/classes/class_javaclasswrapper.rst
Summary: JavaClassWrapper singleton enables Godot to send and receive data through the Java Native Interface (JNI) on Android builds.

Note: This singleton is only available in Android builds.

GDScript:
    var LocalDateTime = JavaClassWrapper.wrap("java.time.LocalDateTime")
    var DateTimeFormatter = JavaClassWrapper.wrap("java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter")

    var datetime = LocalDateTime.now()
    var formatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("dd-MM-yyyy HH:mm:ss")

    print(datetime.format(formatter))

Warning: When calling Java methods, be sure to check get_exception() to check if the method threw an exception.
