Document: JavaClassWrapper
Path: godot/classes/class_javaclasswrapper.rst
Summary: JavaClassWrapper methods for retrieving Java exceptions and wrapping Java classes for Godot interaction.

JavaObject get_exception()  
Returns the Java exception from the last call into a Java class. If no exception occurred, returns null. Note: Only functional on Android platforms.

JavaClass wrap(String name)  
Wraps a Java class for Godot interaction, returning it as a JavaClass Object. Use $ instead of . for nested classes (e.g., "android.view.WindowManager$LayoutParams"). Note: On non-Android platforms, returns empty JavaClass. To invoke constructors, call methods with the same name as the class:

GDScript:
	var Intent = JavaClassWrapper.wrap("android.content.Intent")
	var intent = Intent.Intent()